todoapp.model

Class ToDoList

  • java.lang.Object
    • todoapp.model.ToDoList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ToDoList
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A ToDoList has several properties such as a listName, category, creationTime, a deadline which is made up of a LocalDate and LocalTime, and an associated list of tasks which represent the ToDoList items to be completed.
    See Also:

      • ToDoList

        public ToDoList(java.lang.String listName,
                java.lang.String category,
                java.time.LocalDate deadlineDate,
                java.time.LocalTime deadlineTime)
        The ToDoList constructor initializes a new instance of a ToDolist. The listName, category, deadlineDate, and deadlineTime are passed to the ToDoList constructor at creation time while the actual creationTime field and the ArrayList of Tasks are automatically initialized to the current LocalDateTime and an empty ArrayList respectively.
